-- Commerce Minister Chen Says China Opening Policies Face Foreign Challenges
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-29T06:53:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/commerce-minister-chen-says-china-opening-policies-face-foreign-challenges.html
China’s opening-up policies are
facing challenges because of overseas pressure on the value of
the yuan, domestic innovation rules and foreign investment,
Minister of Commerce Chen Deming said in an article published on
the ministry’s website today.  The nation is also facing domestic challenges such as
rising labor costs, according to the article. China will work to
enhance the value of its exports, Chen said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
